remarks.format: ## Remarks 使用 覆盖一组 对象的行为。Use the to override the behavior of a set of objects. 可以将 类的多个实例应用于一个类成员，前提是每个实例都有一个不同的 属性值;这会指示 将命名元素下的未知元素收集到相应的数组中。Multiple instances of the class can be applied to a class member, as long as each instance has a distinct property value; this instructs the to collect unknown elements under the named element into the appropriate array. 出于此原因，可以将 类的多个实例添加到 中。It is for this reason that multiple instances of the class can be added to the . 若要重写一组 对象：To override a set of objects: 1. 创建 。Create an . 2. 创建一组 对象，并使用 方法将每个对象添加到集合中。Create the set of objects, and add each object to the collection using the method. 3. 创建 。Create an . 4. 将 属性设置为 。Set the property to the . 5. 创建 。Create an . 6. 使用 方法将 添加到 。Add the to the using the method. 7. 使用 创建 的实例。Create an instance of the using the . 8. 序列化或反序列化包含一组 对象的对象。Serialize or deserialize an object that contains the set of objects. ## Examples 下面的示例创建一个新 ，并将其添加到通过 属性访问的对象的集合中。The following example creates a new and adds it to the collection of objects accessed through the property. 然后，将 添加到用于创建 的 。The is then added to a which is used to create an . 用于序列化或反序列化对象。The is used to serialize or deserialize an object. 若要查看使用 属性的效果，请通过在 `Main` 方法中运行 `SerializeObject` 方法来创建名为 UnknownElements 的 XML 文档。To see the effect of using the property, create an XML document named UnknownElements.xml by running the `SerializeObject` method in the `Main` method. 编辑生成的文档以包含其他（未知）元素。Edit the resulting document to include other (unknown) elements. 注释掉 `Main` 方法中的 `SerializeObject` 调用，取消注释对 `DeserializeObject` 方法的调用，该方法输出任何未知 XML 元素的名称和值。Comment out the `SerializeObject` call in the `Main` method, and uncomment the call to the `DeserializeObject` method, which prints out the name and value of any unknown XML element.
